nto a large bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place ginger and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>."},{"content":"Add mushrooms, spring onions\/shallots, water chestnuts and carrots and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer into bowl with cabbage and stir well to combine."},{"content":"Place sesame oil into mixing bowl and heat <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add mince, prawns, soy sauce, salt, pepper and cornflour. Stir with aid of spatula, then sauté <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer into bowl with chopped vegetables and stir to combine."},{"content":"Place 1 spring roll pastry sheet on a clean work surface with 1 corner facing you (in a diamond shape). Place 2 tablespoons of the filling in top corner of pastry sheet. Roll pastry over until it covers the filling; fold side corners in to create a roll (approx. 12-14 cm wide), then continue rolling to the bottom corner and seal. If needed, brush a little water on the edge to help seal the ends. Transfer onto a large plate and repeat with remaining pastry sheets and filling."},{"content":"Place a deep saucepan over high heat and fill three-quarters full with oil. Working in batches, brush spring rolls with egg wash and carefully place into hot oil. Fry for  3-5 minutes or until golden all over. Using a slotted spoon, carefully remove from oil and drain on paper towels. Serve hot with reserved Sweet and sour sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can find spring roll pastry sheets in the frozen food aisle of most major supermarkets or from Asian food stores. Ensure that you purchase spring roll pastry sheets; rice vermicelli sheets will not work in this recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h","1h 20m","20 portions"]}